@patrick-schultz your assignment was totally random!

Here is the code for TableDistinct:
```scala
case class TableDistinct(child: TableIR) extends TableIR {

  ...

  protected[ir] override def execute(hc: HailContext): TableValue = {
    val prev = child.execute(hc)
    prev.copy(rvd = prev.rvd.distinctByKey())
  }
}
```

I suspect that if the RVD key is longer than the table `typ.key`, this is going to produce incorrect results.
